							<section data-markdown  style =  "text-align: left;font-size: 75%">
					Low income households are the most concerned:
					1. Variation in income.
					2. Small marginal tax brackets (when including benefits).  
					3. Concave utility $\implies$ steep at the bottom.  
					(For low income households, big utility gains implies small money metric gains).
					4. Behaviors related to savings.
					</section>
